      "index": "aJ",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2095914812,
      "version": 224,
      "versionNonce": 1794323275,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775334275199,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "ABI --- Application Binary Interface: \n\n\nthis is how binary code interfaces with each other\nat the machine level  --- you know .. our GNU is an ABI",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "ABI --- Application Binary Interface: \n\n\nthis is how binary code interfaces with each other\nat the machine level  --- you know .. our GNU is an ABI",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "rwtRasxrRRzFrFe0D5THF",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -2462.689080980089,
      "y": 26.370181189643063,
      "width": 824.9990234375,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aK",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1080764804,
      "version": 344,
      "versionNonce": 1468316389,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775334275199,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "LINKER:\n\n- links all the functions and other things to their definitions\n- assigns memory address to stuff so that the compiler where to store what \n- combines code and data into a single binary that the os can execute",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "LINKER:\n\n- links all the functions and other things to their definitions\n- assigns memory address to stuff so that the compiler where to store what \n- combines code and data into a single binary that the os can execute",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "8kOTPoeNguiUSR2cB57mg",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -2463.7382600572373,
      "y": 214.1731558905708,
      "width": 857.9989013671875,
      "height": 225,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aL",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2081878532,
      "version": 156,
      "versionNonce": 1550094827,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775334275199,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "LANGUAGE ITEMS:\n\n\nthings that tell the compiler to do specific stuff when asked for something...\n\nthey the stuff is unique and guaranteed to exist ...\nif you provide multiple implementation of the stuff, you run into errors ....\n\ncheck out \"copy\", \"start\" and \"eh_personality\" in rust ...",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "LANGUAGE ITEMS:\n\n\nthings that tell the compiler to do specific stuff when asked for something...\n\nthey the stuff is unique and guaranteed to exist ...\nif you provide multiple implementation of the stuff, you run into errors ....\n\ncheck out \"copy\", \"start\" and \"eh_personality\" in rust ...",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "d8GcmQdyeTxmqp9sDdyva",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -2469.7705781724717,
      "y": 485.64849005805127,
      "width": 934.9989624023438,
