    {
      "id": "fekyJFCaOtFJX4W_d7REB",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -3987.024753506918,
      "y": -201.70591205516286,
      "width": 1066.9986572265625,
      "height": 375,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "dotted",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aT",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1300919840,
      "version": 1274,
      "versionNonce": 1371644005,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775334275199,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "BOOTLOADERS:\n\nOn startup the BIOS starts and runs some self-tests ..\nafter that it transfers control to the bootloader which is some exe code \nlocated at the beginning 512 bytes .. sometimes larger so 512 filled first then\nthe second part is kept somewhere else .. \n\nthe bootloader has to find the location of the kernel image on the disk and load\nit into memory -- also has to switch between the modes like REAL, PROTECTED and LONG\n-- it also has to query some information from BIOS like mem maps and pass them onto the OS kernel\n\nMULTIBOOT is a standard for bootloaders that defines \nhow the bootloader interfaces with the operating system..\n\nany multiboot-compliant bootloader can load any multiboot-compliant OS",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "BOOTLOADERS:\n\nOn startup the BIOS starts and runs some self-tests ..\nafter that it transfers control to the bootloader which is some exe code \nlocated at the beginning 512 bytes .. sometimes larger so 512 filled first then\nthe second part is kept somewhere else .. \n\nthe bootloader has to find the location of the kernel image on the disk and load\nit into memory -- also has to switch between the modes like REAL, PROTECTED and LONG\n-- it also has to query some information from BIOS like mem maps and pass them onto the OS kernel\n\nMULTIBOOT is a standard for bootloaders that defines \nhow the bootloader interfaces with the operating system..\n\nany multiboot-compliant bootloader can load any multiboot-compliant OS",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "kM0GDxv_z6Hi4aP3oMhku",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": -4006.8168361692547,
      "y": -221.7877826353252,
      "width": 1117.749237572326,
      "height": 421.48040297685833,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
